    "description": "An M5 feature family carries a Stable (or LTS) public claim only when its proof-corpus plan is complete, the proof packet is current within its freshness SLO, any waiver is unexpired, every required corpus item is present and reviewed or published, the owner is signed off, and the public claim it backs is itself at or above the cutline. A family that loses any of those must drop below the cutline rather than inherit an adjacent green family."
